THOUGHT: The crash occurs in BasicTTIImplBase::getIntrinsicInstrCost when it unconditionally accesses I->getParent()->getParent()->hasOptSize() for the powi intrinsic. During vectorization cost modeling, the intrinsic instruction may not be inserted into a basic block, making I->getParent() null and causing a segfault. I will patch BasicTTIImpl.h to guard this access by using I->getFunction() only if the instruction exists and is attached; otherwise, treat it as not optimized for size. Then I’ll submit the patch.

```bash
applypatch << 'PATCH' && submit-patch
*** Begin Patch
*** Update File: llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/BasicTTIImpl.h
@@
     switch (IID) {
     default:
       break;

     case Intrinsic::powi:
       if (auto *RHSC = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Args[1])) {
-        bool ShouldOptForSize = I->getParent()->getParent()->hasOptSize();
+        // During cost modeling, the intrinsic instruction may be created
+        // transiently and not be inserted into any basic block yet. Accessing
+        // its parent unconditionally can crash. Use getFunction() only if the
+        // instruction exists and is attached; otherwise, assume not opt-size.
+        const Function *F = I ? I->getFunction() : nullptr;
+        bool ShouldOptForSize = F && F->hasOptSize();
         if (getTLI()->isBeneficialToExpandPowI(RHSC->getSExtValue(),
                                                ShouldOptForSize)) {
           // The cost is modeled on the expansion performed by ExpandPowI in
           // SelectionDAGBuilder.
           APInt Exponent = RHSC->getValue().abs();
*** End Patch
